			<div class="content" id="post-content-4866011">
									

<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights:</strong> Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type:</strong> SCP Article</p>
<p><strong>Genre:</strong> Drama</p>
<p><strong>Page Layout:</strong> A series of incident and experiment logs.</p>
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong> Through a series of accidental occurrences, mental and environmental manipulation the foundation slowly discovers the horrifying and for some readers humorous extent a human individual will go through in order to reach his desired target, a suitable bed. Definition of suitable is affected by many factors and perceptions.</p>
<p><strong>Central Narrative:</strong> Incident logs detail a series of increasingly frustrating disappearances for seemingly innocuous reasons that tie into a series of experiments of increasing complexity and difficulty/danger. Including discovery of suspect as result of jail cells bring unable to hold a man convicted of a massive series of breaking and entering.</p>
<p><strong>Hook/Attention-Grabber:</strong> Starting with the discovery of the test subject and first incident logs it's immediately apparent that a perfect Houdini has been combined with massive property damage. No lock to complex no wall too strong no bridge to far to stop this man from sleeping. Attempts are made to use this power for unstoppable infiltration.</p>
<p><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> While leaving room for imagination it's hinted the subject is suffering from the results of a &quot;Monkeys Paw&quot; wish that included a specified sleeping time. Exact wording is never discovered but it's hinted at including that the subject may be much older than he looks.</p>

