														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4866132">
									

<p>Hello Tarastie,<br />
Echoing the words of fluffal above, I am not an official reviewer either. That said, while you seem somewhat dismissive of the feedback of non-reviewers, so I will be blunt; the concept and narrative needs to be more fleshed out. Obviously I cannot speak on their behalf, but I think that most reviewers will have a difficult time giving out a coveted greenlight without knowing more details.</p>
<p>All that out of the way, I do think you have a good idea at it's core and I think can see the direction you are going. So here are some questions and comments on your concept to hopefully get the ball rolling.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Let's&nbsp;dive&nbsp;in</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Let's&nbsp;un-dive&nbsp;in</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>1. How &quot;human&quot; is the entity. I know you alluded to them having super-strenght and maybe even being immortal possibly, but aside from that; what is their character. Is the aware of his anomaly. I think most people if they discovered that they went into a rampage if they didnt get to bed in time, they'd take extra precautions to make sure it doesn't happen.<br />
2. If I understand correctly; the bed in question can change? That does make containment more difficult, but at the moment it seems exactly that, keter-fication without a reason. You seem to have a narrative you are weaving in regards to this but you don't want to give away the surprise; which I understand. However, I think you need to provide at least a little more detail into the facet of his anomaly to get others on board.<br />
3. As stated prior, the details on the narrative itself seem to either not be fleshed out enough or you are withholding them. As such, it is difficult to give a proper review of this. That said, I think the background of this character could provide some interesting narrative and at the moment is mostly being chalked up to &quot;a wish&quot;. Now depending on if you can justify your current narrative, this could be a moot point; but it is something that I think could be expanded on.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>That is my review for now. I think you have something here; it just needs to be put on paper more.<br />
- VoxStulti</p>

